cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper is about using deep neural networks for sequence learning, specifically for mapping sequences to sequences. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses the use of Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks, which are a type of recurrent neural network (RNN) commonly used in language modeling and other sequence learning tasks. This suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of the LSTM for translation tasks, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) if the translation involves image captioning or other visual tasks.
